item.title: Managed Code vs Unmanaged Code
item.description: As a .NET developer, you may hear or see the terms “managed code” and “unmanaged code” from time to time. You may even be asked about them in job interviews. They are terms that can often be overlooked by new .NET developers that are just starting to learn. I think it’s important to at least have a high-level idea of the two terms so I whipped up this blog post to try and illustrate.
